18/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The country marked the tenth anniversary Monday (August 17th) of an earthquake measuring 7.4 on the Richter scale that rocked the Istanbul region, killing more than 17,000 people. Although a decade has passed, about 400 buildings remain destroyed in the epicentre, Koceali. More than 2,000 jobs lost in 1999 have not been recovered either. (BNR, Zaman, ITAR-TASS, Al Jazeera - 17/08/09)
